<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="705" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram in
                            cipher—paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-24"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Hay inquires whether Mr. Choate needs a certified copy of the <hi rend="italic">Mashona’s</hi> manifest, received by the Department of
                            State from the collector of customs at New York?]</p>
                    </div>
